tafsir[5]{c,v,t}:
  9,118,"This shows that the testimony of non-Muslim witnesses in cases involving Muslims is appropriate only when no Muslim is available as a witness."
  9,119,"This refers to the Day of Judgement."
  9,120,"The reference here is to the response of the world to the call of the Prophets."
  9,121,"This reply indicates that the Prophets would say that their knowledge was confined to that limited, outward response which they had encountered during their lifetimes. The true reaction to their call at various places and in different forms would only be known completely to God Himself."
  9,122,"The initial question would be addressed to all Prophets as such. Then each of them would be called upon to bear witness separately, as stated in several places in the Qur'an. In this connection the question that will be addressed to Jesus is specifically mentioned here."